


sites(1)             GRASS Reference Manual              sites(1)



NAME
     sites - Accesses information regarding sites

SYNOPSIS
     sites

OVERVIEW
     The sites program provides the user with the capability of
     interfacing site data with the geographic data in Two
     spatial analysis reports of the sites are available, as well
     as an interface to the S statistical package.

DESCRIPTION
     The sites program is a site server, providing options for
     the manipulation of site A site is a list of eastings and
     northings describing the of some point feature.  The user
     selects functions from a menu of functions.

     The main menu is:

        SITES MAIN MENU    (current list: no sites)

        LOCATION: spearfish    WINDOW 4928000.00(N)  4914000.00(S) 100.00 (RES)
        MAPSET:   PERMANENT            609000.00(E)   590000.00(W) 100.00 (RES)
        MASK:  none

        Please select one of the following

           1  Get an existing site map
           2  Mask current site map
           3  Save the current site map in your mapset

           4  Check site map for duplicate sites
           5  Edit site map using a UNIX editor

           6  Convert site map to cell map (0/1)
           7  Convert site map to cell map (frequency of occurrence)

           8  Run reports on the current site map


        stop  Leave the SITES program

   At the top of the menu is general information about the
   MAPSET, LOCATION, etc.  Note the above message in parentheses
   "current list:  no sites."  This message will vary depending
   on the status of the list. For example, after getting the
   existing site "arch_sites," the message would read (given the
   window indicated): "current list: 25 sites, 24 in current
   window."





